.TH "ir_establish_scancode" 9 "ir_establish_scancode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ir_establish_scancode \- set a keycode in the scancode->keycode table
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" ir_establish_scancode
.BI "(struct rc_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "struct rc_map *rc_map "  ","
.BI "u64 scancode "  ","
.BI "bool resize "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the struct rc_dev device descriptor
.IP "rc_map" 12
scancode table to be searched
.IP "scancode" 12
the desired scancode
.IP "resize" 12
controls whether we allowed to resize the table to
accommodate not yet present scancodes
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine is used to locate given scancode in rc_map.
If scancode is not yet present the routine will allocate a new slot
for it.
.SH "RETURN"
index of the mapping containing scancode in question
or -1U in case of failure.
